WEBVTT

1
00:01:30.560 --> 00:01:35.080
GAME OF THRONES

2
00:01:36.600 --> 00:01:39.160
Episode 10

3
00:02:02.320 --> 00:02:04.520
Look at me!

4
00:02:05.040 --> 00:02:08.120
Remember me. boy?
Remember me now?

5
00:02:08.800 --> 00:02:10.800
There's a smart boy.

6
00:02:11.640 --> 00:02:15.560
You'll be coming with me. boy.
And you'll be keeping your mouth shut.

7
00:02:32.120 --> 00:02:34.480
- Keep your mouth shut. boy.
- I'm not a boy.

8
00:02:35.040 --> 00:02:37.720
Not a smart boy.
that what you're trying to say?

9
00:02:37.880 --> 00:02:39.840
Do you want to live. boy?

10
00:02:43.280 --> 00:02:45.600
North. boy.
We're going north.

11
00:03:17.400 --> 00:03:19.320
It had three eyes.

12
00:03:19.560 --> 00:03:21.680
It told me to come with him.
so I did.

13
00:03:22.680 --> 00:03:24.640
We went down
into the crypts...

14
00:03:24.800 --> 00:03:26.440
And my father was there.

15
00:03:26.560 --> 00:03:28.720
Your father's not down there
little lord.

16
00:03:28.800 --> 00:03:30.880
Not for many years yet.

17
00:03:32.160 --> 00:03:34.800
You're afraid. Just like Hodor.

18
00:03:35.160 --> 00:03:37.240
I'm not afraid of some hole
in the ground.

19
00:03:37.320 --> 00:03:40.080
You've lived beyond the Wall.
What are you scared of?

20
00:03:40.880 --> 00:03:43.400
I'm a crippled boy
and I'm willing to go there.

21
00:03:48.520 --> 00:03:50.680
That's my grandfather.
Lord Rickard.

22
00:03:51.520 --> 00:03:53.880
He was burned alive
by Mad King Aerys.

23
00:03:55.480 --> 00:03:57.640
That's Lyanna.
my father's sister.

24
00:03:58.160 --> 00:04:00.240
King Robert was supposed
to marry her.

25
00:04:00.360 --> 00:04:02.520
but Rhaegar Targaryen
kidnapped her.

26
00:04:03.720 --> 00:04:05.880
Robert started a war
to win her back.

27
00:04:05.960 --> 00:04:08.440
He killed Rhaegar.
but she died anyway.

28
00:04:09.960 --> 00:04:12.200
That's where I saw father.

29
00:04:13.520 --> 00:04:15.960
You see? He's not here...

30
00:04:24.240 --> 00:04:26.120
Here. Shaggydog.

31
00:04:26.240 --> 00:04:27.880
Rickon!

32
00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:30.800
That beast is supposed to be
chained in the kennels...

33
00:04:31.120 --> 00:04:32.880
He doesn't like chains.

34
00:04:33.000 --> 00:04:35.440
What are you doing down here?
Come back up with us.

35
00:04:35.520 --> 00:04:37.480
No. I came to see father.

36
00:04:37.560 --> 00:04:40.200
How many times have I told you.
he's in King's Landing

37
00:04:40.320 --> 00:04:42.240
with Sansa and Arya...

38
00:04:42.360 --> 00:04:44.360
He was down here.
I saw him.

39
00:04:44.680 --> 00:04:48.640
- Saw him when?
- Last night. When I was sleeping.

40
00:04:50.320 --> 00:04:52.240
Here. Shaggydog!

41
00:04:57.720 --> 00:05:01.040
You both miss him.
It's only natural he'd be

42
00:05:01.200 --> 00:05:05.520
in your thoughts and dreams.
but that doesn't mean that...

43
00:05:07.520 --> 00:05:09.320
Bran...

44
00:05:27.720 --> 00:05:30.440
My Lady...

45
00:06:21.200 --> 00:06:22.920
Robb.

46
00:06:24.080 --> 00:06:25.720
Robb!

47
00:06:34.560 --> 00:06:36.360
You've ruined your sword.

48
00:06:49.920 --> 00:06:53.800
I'm going to kill them all.
Every one of them.

49
00:06:55.840 --> 00:06:57.920
I'll kill them all.

50
00:06:59.360 --> 00:07:01.240
My boy...

51
00:07:03.280 --> 00:07:05.400
They have your sisters.

52
00:07:07.080 --> 00:07:09.080
We have to get
the girls back.

53
00:07:11.000 --> 00:07:13.360
And then
we'll kill them all.

54
00:07:19.880 --> 00:07:22.880
The boar's great tusks.
they boded ill

55
00:07:24.480 --> 00:07:26.800
for good King Robert's health.

56
00:07:28.120 --> 00:07:30.280
And the beast was every bit
as fat

57
00:07:31.720 --> 00:07:33.520
as Robert was himself.

58
00:07:35.320 --> 00:07:38.000
But our brave king cried.
Do your worst !

59
00:07:38.960 --> 00:07:40.760
I'll have your ugly head !

60
00:07:42.160 --> 00:07:44.600
You're nowhere near
as murd'rous as

61
00:07:47.240 --> 00:07:49.840
the lion in my bed.

62
00:07:50.960 --> 00:07:53.400
King Robert lost
his battle and

63
00:07:54.800 --> 00:07:57.040
He failed his final test

64
00:07:58.800 --> 00:08:01.840
The lion ripped
his balls off and

65
00:08:05.600 --> 00:08:08.080
the boar did all the rest.

66
00:08:21.400 --> 00:08:23.320
Very amusing!

67
00:08:23.480 --> 00:08:25.320
Isn't it a funny song?

68
00:08:26.320 --> 00:08:28.280
Thank you for the rendition.

69
00:08:28.600 --> 00:08:31.280
I imagine it was even better
received in that tavern.

70
00:08:31.400 --> 00:08:33.200
I'm so sorry. your Grace...

71
00:08:33.320 --> 00:08:35.440
I'll never sing it again.
I swear...

72
00:08:35.560 --> 00:08:38.920
Tell me. which do you favor:
your fingers or your tongue?

73
00:08:40.400 --> 00:08:43.280
- Your Grace?
- Your fingers? Or your tongue?

74
00:08:43.360 --> 00:08:45.640
If you got to keep one.
which would it be?

75
00:08:49.520 --> 00:08:51.600
Or I could just
cut your throat.

76
00:08:52.680 --> 00:08:54.920
I... every man needs hands.
your Grace.

77
00:08:55.040 --> 00:08:58.960
- Good. Tongue it is.
- Your Grace. please. I...

78
00:09:01.280 --> 00:09:04.440
Ser Ilyn. Who better than you
to carry out the sentence?

79
00:09:04.720 --> 00:09:06.560
I beg of you please no...

80
00:09:12.280 --> 00:09:14.840
Your Grace. please.
I'll never sing it again.

81
00:09:15.080 --> 00:09:16.840
I'm done for today.

82
00:09:17.760 --> 00:09:20.040
I leave the rest of the cases
to you. Mother.

83
00:09:22.640 --> 00:09:24.600
Your Grace. please.

84
00:09:32.120 --> 00:09:34.400
You look quite nice.

85
00:09:34.640 --> 00:09:37.520
- Thank you. my lord.
- Your Grace. I'm king now.

86
00:09:41.240 --> 00:09:43.560
Walk with me. I want
to show you something.

87
00:09:48.160 --> 00:09:50.160
Do as you're bid. child.

88
00:09:57.000 --> 00:09:59.920
And as soon as you've had your
blood. I'll put a son in you.

89
00:10:00.000 --> 00:10:02.080
Mother says
it shouldn't be long.

90
00:10:06.440 --> 00:10:08.400
No... please. no.

91
00:10:08.960 --> 00:10:11.800
This one's your father.
this one here.

92
00:10:14.120 --> 00:10:16.440
Look at it and see
what happens to traitors.

93
00:10:16.600 --> 00:10:20.120
- You promised to be merciful!
- I was. I gave him a clean death.

94
00:10:23.160 --> 00:10:24.920
Look at him.

95
00:10:25.040 --> 00:10:27.960
Please. let me go home. I won't
do any treason. I swear it...

96
00:10:28.040 --> 00:10:31.640
Mother says I'm still to marry you.
so you'll stay here. and obey.

97
00:10:34.160 --> 00:10:36.120
Look at him!

98
00:10:44.280 --> 00:10:46.920
- Well?
- How long do I have to look?

99
00:10:49.840 --> 00:10:51.800
As long as it pleases me.

100
00:10:54.640 --> 00:10:57.560
- Do you want to see the rest?
- If it please your Grace.

101
00:10:59.000 --> 00:11:01.320
That's you Septa. there.

102
00:11:02.640 --> 00:11:05.360
I'll tell you what: I'm going
to give you a present.

103
00:11:06.400 --> 00:11:09.440
After I raise my armies
and kill your traitor brother.

104
00:11:09.880 --> 00:11:12.000
I'm going to give you
his head as well.

105
00:11:13.000 --> 00:11:15.160
Or maybe
he will give me yours.

106
00:11:20.400 --> 00:11:23.200
My mother tells me a king
should never strike his lady.

107
00:11:24.280 --> 00:11:26.080
Ser Meryn.

108
00:11:46.600 --> 00:11:48.680
Here. girl.

109
00:11:52.200 --> 00:11:55.600
Will you obey now?
Or do you need another lesson?

110
00:11:59.880 --> 00:12:01.760
I'll look for you in court.

111
00:12:04.640 --> 00:12:07.840
Save yourself some pain. girl.
Give him what he wants.

112
00:12:10.640 --> 00:12:12.680
You'll be needing that again.

113
00:12:32.680 --> 00:12:35.920
The proper course is clear:
pledge fealty to King Renly

114
00:12:36.200 --> 00:12:38.520
and move south to join
our forces with his.

115
00:12:40.080 --> 00:12:41.640
Renly is not the king.

116
00:12:42.480 --> 00:12:44.760
You cannot mean to hold
to Joffrey. my lord.

117
00:12:44.920 --> 00:12:48.040
- He put your father to death.
- That doesn't make Renly king.

118
00:12:48.840 --> 00:12:52.760
He's Robert's youngest brother.
Bran can't be lord of Winterfell

119
00:12:52.840 --> 00:12:55.720
before me. and Renly
can't be king before Stannis.

120
00:12:56.320 --> 00:12:58.480
So do you mean
to declare us for Stannis?

121
00:13:00.040 --> 00:13:02.360
My lords!

122
00:13:04.000 --> 00:13:06.160
Here is what
I say to these two kings!

123
00:13:09.520 --> 00:13:13.720
Renly Baratheon is nothing
to me. nor Stannis neither.

124
00:13:14.560 --> 00:13:18.000
Why should they rule over me
and mine. from some flowery seat

125
00:13:18.280 --> 00:13:22.720
in the south? What do they know
of the Wall or the wolfs wood?

126
00:13:24.160 --> 00:13:26.200
Even their gods are wrong!

127
00:13:29.600 --> 00:13:31.760
Why shouldn't we rule
ourselves again?

128
00:13:32.960 --> 00:13:37.440
It was the dragons we bowed to.
and now the dragons are all dead!

129
00:13:39.600 --> 00:13:43.840
There sits the only king I mean
to bend my knee to.

130
00:13:45.640 --> 00:13:47.520
The King of the North!

131
00:13:54.920 --> 00:13:57.160
I'll have peace
on those terms.

132
00:13:57.480 --> 00:14:01.040
They can keep their red castle
and their iron chair. too.

133
00:14:03.520 --> 00:14:05.800
The King in the North!

134
00:14:06.800 --> 00:14:10.320
- Am I your brother. now and always?
- Now and always.

135
00:14:14.880 --> 00:14:17.600
My sword is yours.
in victory and defeat.

136
00:14:18.320 --> 00:14:20.480
from this day
until my last day.

137
00:14:21.920 --> 00:14:24.080
The King in the North!

138
00:14:49.880 --> 00:14:53.480
- Lady Stark.
- I want to see him. Now!

139
00:15:14.840 --> 00:15:16.600
Leave us.

140
00:15:21.440 --> 00:15:25.080
You look lovely tonight.
Lady Stark. Widowhood becomes you.

141
00:15:28.760 --> 00:15:31.440
Your bed must be lonely.
Is that why you came?

142
00:15:33.720 --> 00:15:36.280
I'm not at my best but I think
I could be of service.

143
00:15:38.280 --> 00:15:40.720
Slip out of that gown
and we'll see if I'm up to it.

144
00:15:46.480 --> 00:15:50.120
- I do like a violent woman.
- I'll kill you tonight. ser.

145
00:15:51.560 --> 00:15:54.560
Pack your head in a box
and send it to your sister.

146
00:15:54.800 --> 00:15:57.680
Let me show you how.
Hit me again. over the ear.

147
00:15:58.440 --> 00:16:00.320
And again. and again.

148
00:16:01.400 --> 00:16:04.040
You're stronger than you look.
it shouldn't take long.

149
00:16:04.120 --> 00:16:06.240
That is what you'd like the world
to believe.

150
00:16:06.320 --> 00:16:08.160
that you don't fear death.

151
00:16:08.280 --> 00:16:10.800
But I don't.
The dark is coming for all of us.

152
00:16:10.960 --> 00:16:12.640
Why cry about it?

153
00:16:12.760 --> 00:16:16.600
Because you're going to the deepest
of the seven hells. if the gods just.

154
00:16:17.280 --> 00:16:21.240
What gods are those?
The trees your husband prayed to?

155
00:16:22.640 --> 00:16:25.960
Where were the trees when he was
getting his head chopped off?

156
00:16:26.160 --> 00:16:28.680
If your gods are real.
and if they are just.

157
00:16:29.600 --> 00:16:32.000
why is the world
so full of injustice?

158
00:16:33.120 --> 00:16:35.280
Because of men like you.

159
00:16:37.040 --> 00:16:39.960
There are no men like me.
Only me.

160
00:16:46.200 --> 00:16:48.200
My son. Bran.

161
00:16:49.680 --> 00:16:51.800
How did he come
to fall from that tower?

162
00:16:52.080 --> 00:16:54.080
I pushed him out the window.

163
00:16:56.920 --> 00:16:58.760
Why?

164
00:17:00.160 --> 00:17:03.280
- I hoped the fall would kill him.
- Why?

165
00:17:12.080 --> 00:17:15.120
You should get some sleep.
It's going to be a long war.

166
00:17:40.320 --> 00:17:42.480
I can't believe we are
actually at war.

167
00:17:44.040 --> 00:17:46.800
Was it this exciting last time.
when you were young?

168
00:17:50.400 --> 00:17:52.120
What does it say?

169
00:17:53.480 --> 00:17:56.800
Have we captured Robb Stark yet?
What's our next move?

170
00:17:57.000 --> 00:17:59.800
Shut up
and get back into bed.

171
00:18:09.120 --> 00:18:10.800
They have my son.

172
00:18:13.960 --> 00:18:16.680
The Stark boy appears to be
less green than we'd hoped.

173
00:18:16.800 --> 00:18:19.680
I've heard his wolf killed
a dozen men and as many horses.

174
00:18:19.760 --> 00:18:21.560
Is it true
about Stannis and Renly?!

175
00:18:21.640 --> 00:18:24.080
Both Baratheon brothers
have taken up against us.

176
00:18:24.160 --> 00:18:27.440
Jaime captured. his armies
scattered... it's a catastrophe.

177
00:18:29.040 --> 00:18:30.920
Perhaps we
should sue for peace.

178
00:18:34.960 --> 00:18:38.160
There's your peace. Joffrey saw
to that when he decided

179
00:18:38.240 --> 00:18:40.400
to remove Ned Stark's head.

180
00:18:41.480 --> 00:18:43.960
You'll have an easier time
drinking from that cup

181
00:18:44.040 --> 00:18:46.600
than you will getting Robb Stark
to the table now.

182
00:18:47.000 --> 00:18:49.320
He's winning.
in case you hadn't noticed.

183
00:18:50.200 --> 00:18:52.160
I'm told we still have
his sisters...

184
00:18:52.240 --> 00:18:54.760
The first order of business
is ransoming Ser Jaime.

185
00:18:54.840 --> 00:18:56.800
No truces.
We can't afford to look weak.

186
00:18:56.880 --> 00:18:58.600
We should march on them
at once...

187
00:18:58.680 --> 00:19:00.880
First we need to return
to Casterly Rock...

188
00:19:00.960 --> 00:19:03.480
They have my son.

189
00:19:05.560 --> 00:19:07.440
Get out. All of you.

190
00:19:17.640 --> 00:19:19.440
Not you.

191
00:19:33.960 --> 00:19:35.880
You're right
about Eddard Stark.

192
00:19:38.320 --> 00:19:40.680
If he were alive.
we could have used him to broker

193
00:19:40.760 --> 00:19:43.040
a peace with Winterfell
and Riverrun.

194
00:19:43.160 --> 00:19:46.640
which would have given us time
to deal with Robert's brothers.

195
00:19:47.080 --> 00:19:48.720
But now...

196
00:19:49.800 --> 00:19:52.200
Madness.
Madness and stupidity.

197
00:19:55.600 --> 00:19:57.960
I always thought
you were a stunted fool.

198
00:19:59.840 --> 00:20:02.280
- Perhaps I was wrong.
- Half wrong.

199
00:20:04.880 --> 00:20:08.000
I'm new to strategy. but unless
we want to be surrounded

200
00:20:08.080 --> 00:20:11.040
by three armies.
it appears we can't stay here.

201
00:20:11.480 --> 00:20:13.280
No one is staying here.

202
00:20:14.120 --> 00:20:16.680
Ser Gregor will head out
with five hundred riders

203
00:20:16.760 --> 00:20:19.960
and set the Riverlands on fire
from God's Eye to the Red Fork.

204
00:20:21.000 --> 00:20:23.160
The rest of us will regroup
at Harrenhal.

205
00:20:25.520 --> 00:20:29.320
- And you will go to King's Landing.
- And do what?

206
00:20:30.000 --> 00:20:34.160
Rule. You will serve as Hand
of the King in my stead.

207
00:20:35.360 --> 00:20:38.640
You will bring the boy king
to heel. and his mother. if need be.

208
00:20:38.960 --> 00:20:41.760
And if you get a whiff of treason
from any of the rest:

209
00:20:41.880 --> 00:20:43.800
Baelish. Varys. Pycelle...

210
00:20:43.880 --> 00:20:46.120
Heads. spikes. walls?

211
00:20:46.320 --> 00:20:49.680
Why not my uncle.
or... anyone. Why me?

212
00:20:50.880 --> 00:20:52.920
You're my son.

213
00:21:00.240 --> 00:21:04.240
One more thing: You will not take
the whore to court.

214
00:21:05.720 --> 00:21:07.680
Do you understand?

215
00:21:26.240 --> 00:21:27.960
Ser Jorah...

216
00:21:31.560 --> 00:21:33.800
Gently...

217
00:21:36.520 --> 00:21:39.400
My son... where is he?
I want him.

218
00:21:43.080 --> 00:21:44.840
Where is he?

219
00:21:46.720 --> 00:21:48.560
The boy did not live.

220
00:21:55.320 --> 00:21:57.520
- Tell me.
- What is there to tell?

221
00:21:57.800 --> 00:21:59.880
How did my son die?

222
00:22:02.280 --> 00:22:05.480
He never lived. my princess.
The women say...

223
00:22:06.760 --> 00:22:08.640
What do the women say?

224
00:22:11.320 --> 00:22:14.680
- They say the child was...
- Monstrous. Twisted.

225
00:22:16.200 --> 00:22:17.960
I pulled him out myself.

226
00:22:19.320 --> 00:22:21.880
He was scaled like a lizard.
blind.

227
00:22:22.840 --> 00:22:25.160
with leather wings like
the wings of a bat.

228
00:22:26.320 --> 00:22:28.760
When I touched him the skin fell
from his bones.

229
00:22:29.200 --> 00:22:32.320
inside he was full
of graveworms.

230
00:22:35.120 --> 00:22:38.120
I warned you that only death
can pay for life.

231
00:22:39.440 --> 00:22:41.400
You knew the price.

232
00:22:41.920 --> 00:22:45.160
Where is Khal Drogo?
Show him to me.

233
00:22:46.320 --> 00:22:50.240
Show me what I bought
with my son's life.

234
00:22:51.440 --> 00:22:53.360
As you command. lady.

235
00:22:54.320 --> 00:22:56.400
Come. I will take you to him.

236
00:22:56.760 --> 00:22:59.480
- Time enough for this later.
- I want to see him now.

237
00:23:15.120 --> 00:23:17.000
The khalasar is gone.

238
00:23:17.240 --> 00:23:21.160
A khal who cannot ride is no khal.
The Dothraki follow only the strong.

239
00:23:23.120 --> 00:23:25.000
I'm sorry. my princess.

240
00:23:36.520 --> 00:23:38.320
Drogo...

241
00:23:39.080 --> 00:23:41.000
My sun and stars.

242
00:23:41.320 --> 00:23:43.000
Why is he out here alone?

243
00:23:43.080 --> 00:23:45.280
He seems to like the warmth.
Princess.

244
00:23:49.720 --> 00:23:54.000
He lives. You asked for life.
You paid for life.

245
00:23:54.480 --> 00:23:56.920
This is not life.
When will he be as he was?

246
00:23:57.480 --> 00:24:00.200
When the sun rises in the west
and sets in the east.

247
00:24:00.920 --> 00:24:04.760
When the seas go dry and mountains
blow in the wind like leaves.

248
00:24:20.480 --> 00:24:22.240
Leave us.

249
00:24:23.240 --> 00:24:25.520
I don't want you alone
with this sorceress.

250
00:24:25.800 --> 00:24:28.400
I have nothing more to fear
from this woman.

251
00:24:29.760 --> 00:24:31.520
Go.

252
00:24:36.520 --> 00:24:39.240
You knew what I was buying.
and you knew the price.

253
00:24:40.800 --> 00:24:42.840
It was wrong of them
to burn my temple.

254
00:24:43.120 --> 00:24:44.800
It angered the Great Shepherd.

255
00:24:44.920 --> 00:24:47.280
This was no god's work.
My child was innocent.

256
00:24:47.360 --> 00:24:49.000
Innocent?

257
00:24:49.520 --> 00:24:52.240
He would have been the Stallion
Who Mounts the World.

258
00:24:52.360 --> 00:24:54.000
Now he will burn no cities.

259
00:24:54.080 --> 00:24:56.600
His khalasar will trample
no nations into dust.

260
00:24:56.920 --> 00:25:00.920
- I spoke for you. I saved you.
- Saved me?

261
00:25:03.600 --> 00:25:07.120
Three riders raped me
before you saved me. girl.

262
00:25:10.880 --> 00:25:13.040
I saw my god's house burn.

263
00:25:14.240 --> 00:25:17.080
where I had healed men and women
beyond counting.

264
00:25:18.120 --> 00:25:20.040
In the street
I saw a pile of heads.

265
00:25:20.200 --> 00:25:22.320
The head of the baker
who made my bread.

266
00:25:22.440 --> 00:25:26.040
The head of a boy I had cured
of fever. only three moons past.

267
00:25:26.840 --> 00:25:30.800
Tell me again exactly what it was
that you saved.

268
00:25:32.400 --> 00:25:34.080
Your life.

269
00:25:36.000 --> 00:25:37.840
Look at your khal

270
00:25:39.960 --> 00:25:42.280
and you will see exactly
what life is worth

271
00:25:42.960 --> 00:25:45.040
when all the rest is gone.

272
00:25:57.840 --> 00:25:59.480
You can't.

273
00:26:00.520 --> 00:26:02.120
Get out of the way. Sam.

274
00:26:02.240 --> 00:26:04.960
They'll put out the word.
they'll send out ravens...

275
00:26:05.360 --> 00:26:07.120
people will come after you.

276
00:26:07.320 --> 00:26:09.520
Do you know what happens
to deserters?

277
00:26:12.320 --> 00:26:14.040
Better than you do.

278
00:26:14.800 --> 00:26:17.240
- What are you going to do?
- Find my brother.

279
00:26:18.600 --> 00:26:21.000
And put a sword
through King Joffrey's throat.

280
00:26:22.560 --> 00:26:25.080
You can't leave us now.
We need you here.

281
00:26:26.800 --> 00:26:28.800
- Move.
- I won't let you go.

282
00:26:30.040 --> 00:26:32.040
- Move.
- No.

283
00:26:49.760 --> 00:26:52.760
- Hand of the King.
- So it would seem.

284
00:26:54.200 --> 00:26:56.880
And your father said you couldn't
take anyone with you

285
00:26:56.960 --> 00:26:58.600
to King's Landing.

286
00:26:58.680 --> 00:27:01.400
No. he said I couldn't take you
with me to King's Landing.

287
00:27:01.480 --> 00:27:03.240
He was very specific
on the point.

288
00:27:03.320 --> 00:27:05.800
- He knew my name?
- What?

289
00:27:06.240 --> 00:27:08.720
He said. "Don't bring
Shae to King's Landing"?

290
00:27:09.560 --> 00:27:11.520
I believe he used
the word whore.

291
00:27:13.160 --> 00:27:15.800
Are you ashamed of me?
You're afraid I'm going to dance

292
00:27:15.880 --> 00:27:18.200
around the court
with my tits out?

293
00:27:19.320 --> 00:27:22.160
I'm funny now.
I'm Shae. the funny whore.

294
00:27:24.200 --> 00:27:27.000
My father's probably the most powerful
man in the country.

295
00:27:27.080 --> 00:27:28.680
Certainly the richest.

296
00:27:28.760 --> 00:27:30.960
He's got all Seven Kingdoms
in his pockets.

297
00:27:31.200 --> 00:27:34.920
Everybody everywhere always has
to do exactly what my father says.

298
00:27:37.200 --> 00:27:39.080
He's always been a cunt.

299
00:27:45.720 --> 00:27:48.600
I think the ladies of the court
could learn a great deal

300
00:27:48.680 --> 00:27:50.680
from a girl like you.

301
00:27:52.720 --> 00:27:55.400
Why don't you come with me?
Be the Hand's lady.

302
00:27:58.000 --> 00:28:00.280
Because the King needs a Hand.
and a Hand...

303
00:28:04.960 --> 00:28:07.000
I know what a Hand needs.

304
00:28:20.720 --> 00:28:22.400
Ghost?

305
00:28:44.800 --> 00:28:46.680
Lucky you've got plenty
of padding.

306
00:28:48.200 --> 00:28:50.480
We're taking you back
where you belong.

307
00:28:50.560 --> 00:28:53.400
- I belong with my brother.
- We're your brothers now.

308
00:28:53.480 --> 00:28:55.680
They'll kill you if they find out
you've gone.

309
00:28:55.760 --> 00:28:59.000
They'll kill you if they find out
you've come after me. Go back.

310
00:28:59.080 --> 00:29:02.000
Sam told us everything.
We're sorry about your father.

311
00:29:02.120 --> 00:29:04.520
But it doesn't matter.
You took the oath.

312
00:29:04.600 --> 00:29:06.640
- You can't leave.
- I have to.

313
00:29:06.720 --> 00:29:10.040
- You can't. You said the words.
- I don't care...

314
00:29:10.120 --> 00:29:12.920
Hear my words and bear witness
to my vow.

315
00:29:14.160 --> 00:29:15.640
To hell with all of you.

316
00:29:15.720 --> 00:29:19.800
Now my watch begins.
It shall not end until my death.

317
00:29:20.600 --> 00:29:22.480
I shall live and die
at my post.

318
00:29:22.960 --> 00:29:25.920
- I am the sword in the darkness.
- The watcher on the walls.

319
00:29:26.360 --> 00:29:28.600
The shield that guards
the realms of men.

320
00:29:29.240 --> 00:29:32.000
I pledge my life and honor
to the Night's Watch.

321
00:29:32.800 --> 00:29:35.400
For this night.
and all nights to come.

322
00:30:14.080 --> 00:30:18.000
Do you remember our first ride.
my sun and stars?

323
00:30:22.440 --> 00:30:28.080
If you can hear me in there. if you
haven't gone away. show me.

324
00:30:29.160 --> 00:30:32.880
You're a fighter.
You've always been a fighter.

325
00:30:33.240 --> 00:30:36.240
I need you to fight now.

326
00:30:45.480 --> 00:30:50.360
I know you're very far away.
but come back to me.

327
00:30:51.560 --> 00:30:54.320
my sun and stars.

328
00:31:16.000 --> 00:31:22.720
When the sun rises in the west
and sets in the east...

329
00:31:27.240 --> 00:31:29.720
Then you will return to me.
my sun-and-star.

330
00:32:35.280 --> 00:32:39.600
Kings? Oh. I can tell you
all there is to know about kings.

331
00:32:42.640 --> 00:32:45.280
The thing you need to understand
about kings...

332
00:32:50.760 --> 00:32:55.000
Over the past sixty-seven years.
I've known. truly known

333
00:32:55.880 --> 00:32:58.200
more kings
than any man alive.

334
00:33:00.720 --> 00:33:04.080
They're complicated men.
but I know how to serve them.

335
00:33:06.800 --> 00:33:08.760
and keep on serving them.

336
00:33:11.640 --> 00:33:13.600
Aerys Targaryen.

337
00:33:15.360 --> 00:33:19.120
Of all the thousand thousand maladies
the gods visit upon us.

338
00:33:20.720 --> 00:33:22.880
madness is the worst.

339
00:33:24.280 --> 00:33:27.360
He was a good man.
such a charmer.

340
00:33:29.840 --> 00:33:36.440
To watch him melt away before my eyes.
consumed by dreams of fire and blood.

341
00:33:40.760 --> 00:33:43.720
Robert Baratheon was an entirely
different animal.

342
00:33:44.200 --> 00:33:46.280
A powerful man. a great warrior.

343
00:33:47.800 --> 00:33:49.720
but alas. winning a kingdom

344
00:33:49.840 --> 00:33:53.720
and ruling a kingdom are
rather different things.

345
00:33:55.040 --> 00:33:58.800
It is said that those who go
through life with battle visors down

346
00:34:00.080 --> 00:34:03.600
are often blind to the enemies
at their sides.

347
00:34:07.480 --> 00:34:13.560
Now I serve his son. King Joffrey.
may the gods bless his reign.

348
00:34:15.920 --> 00:34:18.920
He is a capable young man.
with a strong military mind.

349
00:34:20.520 --> 00:34:25.440
Stern... but sternness in the defense
of the realm is no vice.

350
00:34:28.160 --> 00:34:30.920
It is far too soon to know
what manner of king he will be.

351
00:34:31.880 --> 00:34:35.440
but I sense true greatness
on the horizon

352
00:34:36.320 --> 00:34:39.760
for our new king.
True greatness.

353
00:34:46.320 --> 00:34:50.040
- So what's the thing?
- What thing?

354
00:34:51.240 --> 00:34:53.160
About kings. You said:

355
00:34:53.320 --> 00:34:55.840
The thing you need to understand
about kings...

356
00:34:56.520 --> 00:34:58.520
The thing I need to...

357
00:34:58.640 --> 00:35:01.000
When you started. you...
never mind.

358
00:35:03.560 --> 00:35:06.400
- Let me see you out. my dear...
- It's alright. No need.

359
00:35:07.160 --> 00:35:09.200
Yes. yes...
Until next time.

360
00:35:56.840 --> 00:35:59.360
When you imagine yourself up there.
how do you look?

361
00:36:00.200 --> 00:36:02.840
Does the crown fit?
Do all the lords and ladies

362
00:36:03.160 --> 00:36:05.920
simper and bow. the ones who
sneered at you for years?

363
00:36:07.280 --> 00:36:10.040
It's hard for them to simper
and bow without heads.

364
00:36:11.960 --> 00:36:14.080
A man with great ambition
and no morals.

365
00:36:14.200 --> 00:36:15.880
I wouldn't bet against you.

366
00:36:17.360 --> 00:36:19.760
And what would you do. my friend.
if you found yourself

367
00:36:19.840 --> 00:36:21.600
sitting up there?

368
00:36:22.480 --> 00:36:24.360
I must be one of the few men
in this city

369
00:36:24.440 --> 00:36:25.920
who doesnt want to be king.

370
00:36:26.000 --> 00:36:28.920
You must be one of the few men
in this city who isnt a man.

371
00:36:29.480 --> 00:36:31.400
You can do better than that.

372
00:36:35.200 --> 00:36:38.560
When they castrated you. did they
take the pillar with the stones?

373
00:36:38.800 --> 00:36:40.280
I've always wondered.

374
00:36:40.360 --> 00:36:43.640
Have you? Do you spend much time
wondering whats between my legs?

375
00:36:43.720 --> 00:36:48.120
I picture a gash like a woman's.
Is that about right?

376
00:36:48.520 --> 00:36:51.000
I am flattered. of course.
to be pictured at all.

377
00:36:51.520 --> 00:36:54.280
Must be strange for you. even after
all these years.

378
00:36:55.640 --> 00:37:00.920
A man from another land.
despised by most. feared by all.

379
00:37:01.520 --> 00:37:03.200
Am I? That is good to know.

380
00:37:03.320 --> 00:37:05.880
Do you lie awake at night.
fearing my gash?

381
00:37:06.840 --> 00:37:09.800
But you carry on.
whispering in one king's ear

382
00:37:10.320 --> 00:37:11.920
and then the next...

383
00:37:14.840 --> 00:37:17.960
- I admire you.
- And I admire you. Lord Baelish.

384
00:37:19.760 --> 00:37:22.240
A grasper from a minor house
with a major talent

385
00:37:22.480 --> 00:37:25.080
for befriending powerful men.
And women.

386
00:37:25.640 --> 00:37:27.680
A useful talent.
Im sure you'd agree.

387
00:37:29.520 --> 00:37:34.920
So here we stand. In mutual
admiration and respect.

388
00:37:35.840 --> 00:37:39.040
- Playing our roles.
- Serving a new king.

389
00:37:39.760 --> 00:37:41.440
Long may he reign.

390
00:37:41.680 --> 00:37:43.680
My king.

391
00:37:44.840 --> 00:37:46.640
My lords.

392
00:37:47.000 --> 00:37:48.760
Shall we begin?

393
00:37:49.160 --> 00:37:51.720
You're Arry now. hear me?
Arry the orphan boy.

394
00:37:52.880 --> 00:37:55.040
No one asks an orphan
too many questions.

395
00:37:55.160 --> 00:37:57.040
No one gives three shits.

396
00:37:57.560 --> 00:37:59.520
- What's your name?
- Arry.

397
00:38:00.840 --> 00:38:03.160
You got a long way to go
in bad company.

398
00:38:04.440 --> 00:38:07.480
I got twenty this time. men
and boys all bound for the Wall.

399
00:38:08.840 --> 00:38:11.320
Your lord father gave me the pick
of the dungeons.

400
00:38:11.400 --> 00:38:14.040
and I didn't find no little
lordlings down there.

401
00:38:14.720 --> 00:38:17.520
This lot. half of them would turn
you over to the king

402
00:38:17.680 --> 00:38:19.600
quick as spit for a pardon.

403
00:38:19.760 --> 00:38:23.280
The other half would do the same.
only they'd rape you first.

404
00:38:23.840 --> 00:38:26.040
So keep to yourself.
and when you piss.

405
00:38:26.160 --> 00:38:28.120
you do it in the woods.
alone.

406
00:38:29.600 --> 00:38:34.440
You stay with this lot. boy.
And stay. or I'll lock you

407
00:38:34.640 --> 00:38:36.960
in the back of the wagon
with these three.

408
00:38:41.440 --> 00:38:43.240
Watch yourself. midget.

409
00:38:44.560 --> 00:38:46.320
He's got a sword. this one.

410
00:38:46.440 --> 00:38:48.760
What's a gutter rat like you
doing with a sword?

411
00:38:48.840 --> 00:38:50.440
Maybe he's a little squire.

412
00:38:50.520 --> 00:38:52.920
He ain't no squire. look at him.
Looks like a girl.

413
00:38:53.000 --> 00:38:54.760
I bet he stole that sword.

414
00:38:55.960 --> 00:38:57.400
Let's have a look.

415
00:38:59.720 --> 00:39:01.480
I could use me a sword
like that.

416
00:39:01.640 --> 00:39:03.680
- Take it off him.
- Give it here. midget.

417
00:39:03.880 --> 00:39:06.160
Look at him! You better give
Hot Pie the sword.

418
00:39:06.240 --> 00:39:08.000
I've seen him kick
a boy to death.

419
00:39:08.080 --> 00:39:11.440
I knocked him down and I kicked him
in the balls and I kept kicking him

420
00:39:11.520 --> 00:39:13.160
till he was dead.

421
00:39:13.280 --> 00:39:15.080
I kicked him all to pieces.

422
00:39:16.760 --> 00:39:18.360
You better give me that sword.

423
00:39:18.720 --> 00:39:21.000
You want it?
I'll give it to you.

424
00:39:21.640 --> 00:39:23.560
I already killed one fat boy.

425
00:39:24.000 --> 00:39:28.280
I bet you never killed anyone.
I bet you're a liar. But I'm not.

426
00:39:29.000 --> 00:39:31.800
I'm good at killing fat boys.
I like killing fat boys.

427
00:39:34.640 --> 00:39:36.480
You like picking
on the little ones?

428
00:39:37.120 --> 00:39:39.480
I been hammering anvils
the last ten years.

429
00:39:39.760 --> 00:39:43.000
When I hit that steel. it sings.
You gonna sing when I hit you?

430
00:39:50.760 --> 00:39:52.480
That's castle-forged steel.

431
00:39:53.200 --> 00:39:55.720
- Where'd you steal it?
- It was a gift.

432
00:39:56.320 --> 00:39:59.760
Don't matter now. Where we're going.
they don't care what you done.

433
00:40:00.200 --> 00:40:03.680
They got rapers. pickpockets.
highwaymen. murderers.

434
00:40:05.280 --> 00:40:07.680
- Which are you?
- Armorer's apprentice.

435
00:40:09.640 --> 00:40:12.760
My master got sick of me.
So. here I am.

436
00:40:13.480 --> 00:40:15.640
Come on. you sorry sons
of whores!

437
00:40:16.960 --> 00:40:19.360
It's a thousand leagues
from here to the Wall.

438
00:40:19.960 --> 00:40:21.840
and winter is coming!

439
00:40:52.200 --> 00:40:55.600
Ham... How many days in a row
can a person be expected

440
00:40:55.720 --> 00:40:57.800
to start the day with ham?

441
00:40:59.000 --> 00:41:00.640
Get me some beer. at least.

442
00:41:02.920 --> 00:41:06.200
You look exhausted. Was your
moonlight ride that tiring?

443
00:41:10.400 --> 00:41:13.960
Ah. calm yourself. If we beheaded
everyone who ran away for a night.

444
00:41:14.880 --> 00:41:17.080
only ghosts would guard
the Wall.

445
00:41:18.320 --> 00:41:20.520
At least you weren't whoring
in Mole's Town.

446
00:41:21.840 --> 00:41:24.800
Honor made you leave.
Honor brought you back.

447
00:41:26.280 --> 00:41:29.960
- My friends brought me back.
- I didn't say it was your honor.

448
00:41:32.240 --> 00:41:33.640
They killed my father.

449
00:41:33.720 --> 00:41:37.160
And you were going to bring him
back to life? No? Good.

450
00:41:38.200 --> 00:41:40.200
We've had enough
of that sort of thing.

451
00:41:41.720 --> 00:41:45.200
Beyond the Wall. rangers have found
whole villages abandoned.

452
00:41:46.600 --> 00:41:50.320
At night they see fires blazing in
the mountains from dusk until dawn.

453
00:41:51.640 --> 00:41:55.640
A captive wildling swears their tribes
are uniting in some secret stronghold.

454
00:41:56.600 --> 00:41:58.880
to what end the gods only know.

455
00:42:00.240 --> 00:42:04.360
Outside Eastwatch. Cotter Pyke's
men discovered four blue-eyed corpses.

456
00:42:05.040 --> 00:42:08.160
Unlike us. they were wise
enough to burn them.

457
00:42:10.880 --> 00:42:15.080
Do you think your brother's war
is more important than ours?

458
00:42:17.480 --> 00:42:19.120
No.

459
00:42:19.240 --> 00:42:22.200
When dead men or worse come
hunting for us in the night.

460
00:42:22.440 --> 00:42:25.320
do you think it matters
who sits on the Iron Throne?

461
00:42:26.720 --> 00:42:28.480
- No.
- Good.

462
00:42:29.040 --> 00:42:31.240
Because I want you and that wolf
with us

463
00:42:31.680 --> 00:42:33.920
when we go
beyond the Wall tomorrow.

464
00:42:35.280 --> 00:42:36.920
Beyond the Wall?

465
00:42:37.080 --> 00:42:40.280
I will not sit here meekly and wait
for the snows.

466
00:42:40.920 --> 00:42:42.920
I mean to find out
what is happening.

467
00:42:43.800 --> 00:42:46.760
Night's Watch will ride in force
against the wildlings.

468
00:42:47.440 --> 00:42:50.120
the White Walkers.
and whatever else is out there.

469
00:42:53.080 --> 00:42:56.440
And we will find Benjen Stark.
Alive. or dead.

470
00:42:58.120 --> 00:42:59.840
I will command them myself.

471
00:43:00.840 --> 00:43:03.160
So I will only ask you once.
Lord Snow:

472
00:43:05.320 --> 00:43:07.560
Are you a brother
of the Night's Watch

473
00:43:08.040 --> 00:43:10.880
or a bastard boy
who wants to play at war?

474
00:43:44.160 --> 00:43:46.560
Is this your command.
khaleesi?

475
00:43:52.680 --> 00:43:56.360
Drogo will have no use for dragon
eggs in the night lands. Sell them.

476
00:43:57.280 --> 00:44:00.160
You can return to the Free Cities
and live as a wealthy woman

477
00:44:00.240 --> 00:44:01.760
for all your days.

478
00:44:01.840 --> 00:44:03.760
They were not given
to me to sell.

479
00:44:09.120 --> 00:44:11.000
Khaleesi... My queen...

480
00:44:12.320 --> 00:44:15.920
I vow to serve you. to obey you.
to die for you if need be.

481
00:44:17.480 --> 00:44:19.240
But let him go.

482
00:44:19.880 --> 00:44:22.120
I know what you intend.
Do not.

483
00:44:22.680 --> 00:44:26.400
I must.
You don't understand.

484
00:44:27.040 --> 00:44:30.160
Do not ask me to stand aside
as you climb on that pyre.

485
00:44:30.880 --> 00:44:32.840
I will not watch you burn.

486
00:44:34.040 --> 00:44:36.160
Is that what you fear?

487
00:44:54.640 --> 00:44:59.720
You will be my khalasar.
I see the faces of slaves.

488
00:45:01.720 --> 00:45:04.840
I free you.
Take off your collars.

489
00:45:05.200 --> 00:45:07.480
Go if you wish.
noone will stop you.

490
00:45:08.000 --> 00:45:12.800
But if you stay. it will be
as brothers and sisters.

491
00:45:14.000 --> 00:45:15.800
as husbands and wives.

492
00:45:27.760 --> 00:45:29.920
Ser Jorah. bind this woman
to the pyre.

493
00:45:32.640 --> 00:45:34.560
You swore to obey me.

494
00:45:43.320 --> 00:45:47.400
I am Daenerys Stormborn.
of House Targaryen.

495
00:45:48.600 --> 00:45:50.600
of the blood of old Valyria.

496
00:45:50.680 --> 00:45:54.280
I am the dragon's daughter.
and I swear to you

497
00:45:55.640 --> 00:45:58.040
that those who would harm you
will die screaming.

498
00:45:59.480 --> 00:46:01.160
You will not hear me scream.

499
00:46:01.280 --> 00:46:03.040
I will.

500
00:46:04.800 --> 00:46:06.720
But it is not
your screams I want.

501
00:46:08.200 --> 00:46:10.240
Only your life.

502
00:48:34.000 --> 00:48:36.160
Blood of my blood.
